Jesus and his disciples arrived at Capernaum. There, the tax collectors came to Peter and asked him, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
"Yes, he does," he replied. And when Peter came into the house, Jesus spoke first. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "From whom do the kings of the earth collect taxes and duties? From their sons or from others?"
"From others," Peter answered. "Then the sons don't pay," Jesus said to him.
"But we do not want to anger them. Go to the lake and cast your fishing line. Take the first fish you catch. Open its mouth. You will find in it the very coin you need. Take it and give it to them as a tax for me and your brothers."
